\p
\v 21 â\wj No one sews a patch of new, unshrunkenÂŠ23155 clothÂŠ23154 onto an old garmentÂŠ23160, because the new patch will tear away from that old fabric and itÂŠ23172 will end up as a worseÂŠ23181 tear.\wj*
\v 22 \wj And no one puts new wine into old wineskins, because the wine will burstÂŠ23204 the \+add already stretched\+add* wineskins, and thenÂŠ23187 both the wine and the wineskins will be destroyedÂŠ23218. New wine must be put into \+em new\+em* wineskins.\wj*â
