\r (Mat. 13:1-9; Luke 8:4-8)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 4:1: \xt Luk 5:1-3.\x*Again Yeshua started teachingÂŠ24194 by the edge of the lakeÂŠ24198. A hugeÂŠ24209 crowd gatheredÂŠ24200 around him, butÂŠ24190 he had boardedÂŠ24216 a boatÂŠ24215 that was floating in the water, andÂŠ24190 all the people were there on the land.
\v 2 \add âFrom there\add*, he taughtÂŠ24246 them many different things in parablesÂŠ24250, including this one:
\v 3 â\wj ListenÂŠ24263. Once there was a farmer who wentÂŠ24264 to spread some seed.\wj*
\v 4 \wj As he spread it, some landed on the pathÂŠ24281, and the birdsÂŠ24287 came and fed on it.\wj*
\v 5 \wj Some landed on a rockyÂŠ24302 part without a lot of soil, andÂŠ24293 itÂŠ24308 quickly sprouted in the warm, shallow soil,\wj*
\v 6 \wj butÂŠ24327 when the sunÂŠ24332 came up, it dried out becauseÂŠ24336 the roots weren't deep, and so it just witheredÂŠ24341 up.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Some of the seed landed in a thistle patch, and the thistles grew and chokedÂŠ24357 it out, so the plants never bore a crop.\wj*
\v 8 \wj ButÂŠ24365 some seed landed in fertile soil and it bore a harvestâsome of it multiplying thirtyÂŠ24391 times, some sixtyÂŠ24397, and some a hundredÂŠ24403 times.\wj*â
\p
\v 9 ThenÂŠ24405 Yeshua added, â\wj Anyone who wants to understand, let them consider it.\wj*â
