\v 15 \wj and there are some alongÂŠ24522 the pathÂŠ24524 whereÂŠ24526 the good message is beingÂŠ24527 spread, who hear, butÂŠ24519 SatanÂŠ24538 turns up immediatelyÂŠ24535 and snatches the message from them.\wj*
\v 16 \wj Similarly, there's some seed that falls onto rockyÂŠ24566 placesÂŠ24566 where the people who hearÂŠ24572 the good messageÂŠ24574 happily accept itÂŠ24579,\wj*
\v 17 \wj butÂŠ24580 don'tÂŠ24581 make strong rootsâjust temporaryÂŠ24587 \+add changes\+add*. So when they get mocked or attacked about accepting the good messageÂŠ24597, they quickly stumbleÂŠ24600.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Others are the ones where the seed was spread amongÂŠ24609 the thistles. They heardÂŠ24621 the good messageÂŠ24619,\wj*
\v 19 \wj butÂŠ24622 contemporary topics, or the lure of money, or the appetite for otherÂŠ24645 things, choke their good intentions and the messageÂŠ24650 becomesÂŠ24654 unfruitfulÂŠ24652 in them.\wj*
\v 20 \wj ButÂŠ24656 lastly, the seed that landed on the good soil represents the people who hearÂŠ24671 the good messageÂŠ24673, acceptÂŠ24675 it, andÂŠ24656 are fruitfulÂŠ24677 thirtyÂŠ24682, sixtyÂŠ24686, or even a hundredÂŠ24690 times over.\wj*â
