\v 6 SoÂŠ25281 when he had seenÂŠ25282 \nd YeshuaÂŠ25285\nd* in the distance, he ranÂŠ25288 andÂŠ25281 \add as a sign of honour\add* fell to the ground in front of him.
\v 7 Then he called out very loudlyÂŠ25297, âWhat will happen between us, \nd Yeshua\nd*, the son of the highestÂŠ25310 God? I beg you in God's name not to tormentÂŠ25318 me.â
\v 8 BecauseÂŠ25321 Yeshua had already started sayingÂŠ25320, â\wj Come out of the manÂŠ25334 you ungodlyÂŠ25329 spiritÂŠ25327!\wj*â
