\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 6:14-15: \xt Mat 16:14; Mrk 8:28; Luk 9:19.\x*Yeshua was now becoming well known and KingÂŠ26435 HerodÂŠ26436 \add Antipas\add* heardÂŠ26432 about him. He thought that maybe Yohan-the-immerser had come back to life and that's why he was able to do miraclesÂŠ26462.
\p
\v 15 ButÂŠ26473 others thought it was \add the promised return of\add* Eliyah, andÂŠ26473 yet others thought he must be another prophetÂŠ26476 like the ones \add in the Scriptures\add*.
\p
\v 16 But hearing about Yeshua, HerodÂŠ26486 was telling people, âThat Yohan who I had beheadedÂŠ26493, he must have come back to life!â
\v 17 \x + \xo 6:17-18: \xt Luk 3:19-20.\x*BecauseÂŠ26508 HerodÂŠ26510 himselfÂŠ26506 had had Yohan arrested and put in prisonÂŠ26525 becauseÂŠ26508 he had marriedÂŠ26538 HerodiasÂŠ26528, hisÂŠ26534 brotherÂŠ26533 Philip's wifeÂŠ26530.
\v 18 Yohan had been telling him that it was wrong for him to marry his brother'sÂŠ26557 wifeÂŠ26554,
\v 19 andÂŠ26560 so HerodiasÂŠ26561 resentedÂŠ26563 him enough to want to killÂŠ26570 him, butÂŠ26560 Herod hadn't be able to
\v 20 becauseÂŠ26576 he respected Yohan as a righteousÂŠ26584 and holy teacher and so he kept him alive. He often enjoyed hearingÂŠ26601 from Yohan and thought a lot about what he said.
\p
\v 21 However, an opportunityÂŠ26606 came at Herod's birthdayÂŠ26611 celebrationÂŠ26611, when he threw a feast for hisÂŠ26612 top officials and generals and for the leadersÂŠ26624 in GalileeÂŠ26626.
\v 22 The daughterÂŠ26632 of HerodiasÂŠ26636 came in and dancedÂŠ26638 for them, and the king and his party guests all enjoyed it. SoÂŠ26627 the king said to the young woman, âJust ask me for anything and I'llÂŠ26666 give it to you.â
\v 23 And he made an oath, âEven if you asked for half of myÂŠ26690 kingdomÂŠ26689, I'd give it to you!â
\p
\v 24 SoÂŠ26693 she went out andÂŠ26693 asked her mother what she should ask for. HerÂŠ26698 mother told her that she should ask for Yohan's head.
\p
\v 25 SoÂŠ26713 going back into the party, sheÂŠ26722 said seriously to the kingÂŠ26721, âI would like the head of Yohan-the-immerser on a plate!â
\p
\v 26 The kingÂŠ26747 was really upset with that, butÂŠ26743 becauseÂŠ26750 he had made loud oathsÂŠ26752 in front of all his guests, he couldn't say no.
\v 27 SoÂŠ26763 he orderedÂŠ26770 an executionerÂŠ26769 to go out and return with Yohan's head. He went off and beheadedÂŠ26783 him in the prisonÂŠ26787
\v 28 and broughtÂŠ26789 the head into the party on a plate and gave it to the girl, and she gave it to herÂŠ26808 motherÂŠ26807.
\v 29 WhenÂŠ26809 Yohan's followers heardÂŠ26810 about this, they cameÂŠ26815 and fetched hisÂŠ26814 body and put it into a tombÂŠ26828.
\s1 Yeshua feeds 5,000 people
\rem /s1 Miracles of feeding and their significance; Jesus Feeds Five Thousand; Feeding the Five Thousand
\r (Yhn 6:1-14; Mat. 14:13-21; Luke 9:10-17)
\p
\v 30 Now the apprentices who had been sent out returned back to \nd Yeshua\nd* and they reportedÂŠ26837 back everything they had done and what they had been teaching \add people\add*.
\v 31 ThenÂŠ26848 he told them, â\wj Let's just all of us head for a quietÂŠ26861 placeÂŠ26862 and take a break.\wj*â This was becauseÂŠ26870 there were so many people always comingÂŠ26872 and goingÂŠ26875, and sometimes they didn'tÂŠ26878 even have a chance to eatÂŠ26879.
\v 32 SoÂŠ26883 theyÂŠ26885 wentÂŠ26885 by boatÂŠ26890 away to a quietÂŠ26894 placeÂŠ26895 by themselvesÂŠ26899.
\p
\v 33 ButÂŠ26900 people from towns all around had seen them goingÂŠ26904 and recognisedÂŠ26910 who they were, so they ranÂŠ26922 around the lake on footÂŠ26915 and got thereÂŠ26923 aheadÂŠ26925 of them.
\v 34 \x + \xo 6:34: \xt Num 27:17; 1Ki 22:17; 2Ch 18:16; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36.\x*SoÂŠ26933 when Yeshua got out of the boat, he sawÂŠ26938 a big crowdÂŠ26943 andÂŠ26933 felt sorry for them becauseÂŠ26952 they seemed like sheepÂŠ26955 without a shepherdÂŠ26958, so he started teachingÂŠ26962 them many things.
\v 35 ThenÂŠ26966, when it was already getting late, hisÂŠ26977 apprenticesÂŠ26976 came up and said, âThis placeÂŠ26986 is pretty isolated and it's already late.
\v 36 Send these people off now so they can go to the nearby settlements and villagesÂŠ27004 and buy themselvesÂŠ27007 somethingÂŠ27010 to eatÂŠ27012.â
\p
\v 37 ButÂŠ27029 Yeshua answeredÂŠ27019 them, â\wj You give them something to eat.\wj*â
\p They complained, âIf we go, should we buy several months wages worth of bread so we can give all of them something to eat?â
\p
\v 38 ButÂŠ27052 heÂŠ27050 asked, â\wj Go and find out how much bread youÂŠ27059 have.\wj*â
\p WhenÂŠ27052 they'd found out they said, âFive buns and twoÂŠ27072 fish.â
\p
\v 39 Yeshua told all the people to line up in rows andÂŠ27074 sitÂŠ27079 down on the greenÂŠ27090 grassÂŠ27091.
\v 40 SoÂŠ27092 they satÂŠ27093 down in rows of fiftyÂŠ27103 to a hundredÂŠ27099.
\v 41 ThenÂŠ27104 holding the five buns and two fish, he looking up to the skyÂŠ27116 and blessedÂŠ27117 \add God\add*, and thenÂŠ27104 brokeÂŠ27120 up the buns and gave pieces to hisÂŠ27128 apprenticesÂŠ27127 so they could do likewise to the people, and he also dividedÂŠ27139 up the two fish,
\v 42 and all the people ateÂŠ27142 and were satisfiedÂŠ27145.
\v 43 ThenÂŠ27146 theyÂŠ27147 collected the leftover pieces of bread, fillingÂŠ27153 twelveÂŠ27150 basketsÂŠ27152, as well as the leftover pieces of fish.
\v 44 And the headcount of menÂŠ27170 who ate that evening was fiveÂŠ27168 thousandÂŠ27168.
\s1 Yeshua walks on the lake surface
\rem /s1 Jesus Walks on the Water
\r (Yhn 6:15-21; Mat. 14:22-33)
\p
\v 45 Straight after that, Yeshua sent hisÂŠ27177 apprenticesÂŠ27176 off in the boatÂŠ27181 to go acrossÂŠ27188 to BethsaidaÂŠ27190 while he sent the crowdÂŠ27198 home.
\v 46 ThenÂŠ27199 he said goodbyeÂŠ27200 to everyone, andÂŠ27199 climbed the hillÂŠ27205 to pray.
\v 47 Later in the night, the boatÂŠ27213 was out in the middle of the lakeÂŠ27219, andÂŠ27207 only Yeshua remained back there on the land.
\v 48 He saw them struggling to row against the windÂŠ27242, andÂŠ27228 sometime after 3am he came out to them, walkingÂŠ27257 on the lakeÂŠ27262 surface as if to walkÂŠ27257 past them.
\v 49 ButÂŠ27270 they had seenÂŠ27271 someone walkingÂŠ27277 on the lakeÂŠ27276 and thought it was a ghostÂŠ27280, and they yelledÂŠ27285 out
\v 50 becauseÂŠ27287 they had all seen it and were terrified.
\p ButÂŠ27294 Yeshua immediatelyÂŠ27295 spokeÂŠ27296 to them and said, â\wj Hey, take heart, it's me, don'tÂŠ27308 be afraid!\wj*â
\v 51 ThenÂŠ27312 he climbed up into the boatÂŠ27318 andÂŠ27312 the windÂŠ27324 diedÂŠ27322 down. And they were all totally astounded
\v 52 because theyÂŠ27337 hadn't understoodÂŠ27337 the implications of him feeding all the people because theirÂŠ27344 minds were closed.
\s1 Yeshua heals many people around Gennesaret
