\p
\v 1 Some from the Pharisee partyÂŠ27466 andÂŠ27467 some of the law teachersÂŠ27470 had comeÂŠ27471 from Yerushalem to observe Yeshua
\v 2 andÂŠ27474 noticed that some of hisÂŠ27481 followers were eatingÂŠ27490 their food without following their religious customs, i.e., without washing their handsÂŠ27485.
\v 3 (The Pharisees andÂŠ27499, in fact, all the Jewish religious leaders do not eat without first ceremonially washing their handsÂŠ27509 as taught by their eldersÂŠ27519 over the generations.
\v 4 They won'tÂŠ27530 eat at the marketÂŠ27522 if they can'tÂŠ27530 do this first, and have many otherÂŠ27533 regulations about ceremonial washingÂŠ27543 of cups and jugs and copperÂŠ27548 kettlesÂŠ27548.)
\p
\v 5 And the Pharisees andÂŠ27558 religiousÂŠ27560 teachersÂŠ27560 asked Yeshua, âHow come yourÂŠ27568 followers don'tÂŠ27569 follow our Jewish traditionsÂŠ27573, butÂŠ27576 eat without the ceremonial washing of handsÂŠ27582?â
\p
\v 6 And he answeredÂŠ27588, â\wj Yeshayah got it exactly rightÂŠ27592 when he expressed God's thoughts about you hypocritesÂŠ27599 andÂŠ27587 wroteÂŠ27602:\wj*\x + \xo 7:6-7: \xt Isa 29:13 (LXX).\x*
\q1 \wj âThese peopleÂŠ27607 honourÂŠ27613 me with their lipsÂŠ27610,\wj*
\q2 \wj butÂŠ27587 their real desires are far away from mine.\wj*
\q1
\v 7 \wj Their worshipÂŠ27626 of me is worthless,\wj*
\q2 \wj teachingÂŠ27628 man-made rules as if theyÂŠ27626 are from God.â\wj*
\p
\v 8 \wj You've ignored God's commandsÂŠ27647 instead accepting humanÂŠ27655 traditionsÂŠ27653.\wj*â
\p
\v 9 And Yeshua continued, â\wj You all simply dismiss God's commandsÂŠ27673 in favour of yourÂŠ27679 own customs.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 7:10: a \xt Exo 20:12; Deu 5:16; \xo b \xt Exo 21:17; Lev 20:9.\x*\wj Mosheh teaches us,\wj*
\q1 \wj âHonour yourÂŠ27689 parents,â\wj*
\p \wj and\wj*
\q1 \wj âAnyone dishonestly slandering their parents deserves the deathÂŠ27701 penalty.â\wj*
\m
\v 11 \wj But when you all encourage people to sayÂŠ27709, âWhatever I had that may have helped you guys has been given to Godâ,\wj*
\v 12 \wj youÂŠ27730 are actively discouraging them from helping their parentsâ\wj*
\v 13 \wj overriding God's voice for yourÂŠ27751 very convenient teaching that you disseminate instead. And that's not the only example!\wj*â
\s1 Evil comes from inside a person
