\r (Mat. 15:10-20)
\p
\v 14 Yeshua calledÂŠ27765 out to the crowdÂŠ27769, â\wj Everyone listen to me carefully:\wj*
\v 15 \wj Nothing that entersÂŠ27787 your mouth makes you guilty in God's eyes. It's what comes \+em out\+em* of you that demonstrates your culpability.\wj*â
\p
\v 16 â
\v 17 WhenÂŠ27819 Yeshua cameÂŠ27821 back inside, hisÂŠ27835 apprenticesÂŠ27834 asked him what he meant.
\v 18 ButÂŠ27841 he scolded them, â\wj Can't you understandÂŠ27851 something so simple! Can't you see that anything from the outsideÂŠ27856 that entersÂŠ27857 your body doesn't make you guilty in God's sight,\wj*
\v 19 \wj becauseÂŠ27867 it doesn't enterÂŠ27871 your mindÂŠ27876 butÂŠ27882 merely goes into your stomach and ends up in the toilet.\wj*â (By saying this he clearly showed that is was ok for Jews to eat any food.)
\p
\v 20 He continued, â\wj It's what comes out of you that makes you guilty in God's eyes.\wj*
\v 21-22 \wj That's becauseÂŠ27912 evilÂŠ27921 thoughts, sexualÂŠ27924 immoralityÂŠ27924, theftÂŠ27926, murderÂŠ27929, adulteryÂŠ27931, greed, wickedness, deceit, arrogance, lust, slander, pride, and foolishness all come from \+em insideÂŠ27911\+em* people'sÂŠ27917 heartsÂŠ27915 \+add and minds\+add*.\wj*
\v 23 \wj So it's the evilÂŠ27950 that's insideÂŠ27951 a personÂŠ27958 andÂŠ27954 comes out that makes them guilty in God's eyes.\wj*â
