\r (Mat. 15:21-28)
\p
\v 24 Yeshua left that place and wentÂŠ27964 \add up north\add* into the regionsÂŠ27967 of TyreÂŠ27969 and Tsidon. He tried to enter a houseÂŠ27976 without being noticedÂŠ27985 butÂŠ27961 didn'tÂŠ27982 succeed,
\v 25 and straight away a womanÂŠ27993 who had heardÂŠ27991 aboutÂŠ27994 him turned up. She knelt in front of him because she had a littleÂŠ27999 daughterÂŠ27999 who was demon-possessed.
\v 26 The womanÂŠ28019 was GreekÂŠ28021 from PhoeniciaÂŠ28023 in SyriaÂŠ28023 andÂŠ28026 sheÂŠ28027 begged Yeshua to command the demonÂŠ28031 to leave herÂŠ28038 daughterÂŠ28037.
\v 27 ButÂŠ28040 he replied, â\wj Let the \+add Jewish\+add* children be treated firstÂŠ28048, becauseÂŠ28053 it's not good to take the children's food andÂŠ28040 throwÂŠ28066 it to the dogs.\wj*â
\p
\v 28 And she responded, âYes, \nd masterÂŠ28075\nd*, butÂŠ28068 the puppies under the tableÂŠ28086 \em do\em* get to eat the little crumbsÂŠ28092 that the childrenÂŠ28096 drop.â
\p
\v 29 And he answered, â\wj Go home now. As a result of how you just spoke, the demonÂŠ28108 has already left yourÂŠ28112 daughterÂŠ28111.\wj*â
