\v 33 SoÂŠ28185 Yeshua took the man back away from the crowdÂŠ28193, put hisÂŠ28202 fingersÂŠ28201 in the man's earsÂŠ28206, thenÂŠ28185 he spat andÂŠ28185 touchedÂŠ28211 the man's mouth.
\v 34 Looking up to the skyÂŠ28220, he sighed and said, â\wj Open up!\wj*â
\p
\v 35 ThenÂŠ28230 the man could hear, and hisÂŠ28234 tongueÂŠ28246 was released and he began to speakÂŠ28249 properly.
\v 36 The Yeshua advised that they shouldn't tell anyoneÂŠ28255, butÂŠ28262 the more heÂŠ28252 said that, the more they seemed to spread itÂŠ28269 around.
\v 37 The crowds were totally amazedÂŠ28273, sayingÂŠ28274, âHe can do anythingâhe makes the deaf able to hearÂŠ28284, andÂŠ28270 enables the ones who couldn't speakÂŠ28288.â
