\v 4 HisÂŠ28375 apprenticesÂŠ28374 queried, âWhere could anyoneÂŠ28386 find enough food out here in the wildernessÂŠ28392?â
\p
\v 5 He asked, â\wj How much bread have youÂŠ28404 all got?\wj*â
\p âSevenÂŠ28410 buns,â theyÂŠ28407 answered.
\p
\v 6 SoÂŠ28411 Yeshua instructed the crowd to sit down on the groundÂŠ28419. ThenÂŠ28411 he took the sevenÂŠ28423 buns, gave thanksÂŠ28426 and brokeÂŠ28427 them and gave pieces to hisÂŠ28433 apprenticesÂŠ28432 to thenÂŠ28411 distribute to the crowd.
\v 7 They also had a few smallÂŠ28442 cooked fish, so heÂŠ28450 blessedÂŠ28447 them too andÂŠ28444 got them to distribute them as well.
\v 8 After all the people had eaten andÂŠ28463 were full, they collected sevenÂŠ28477 basketfulsÂŠ28478 of leftovers.
\v 9 There were some fourÂŠ28486 thousandÂŠ28486 people there that day, andÂŠ28482 Yeshua sentÂŠ28488 them home after they'd eatenÂŠ28484.
\v 10 And he and hisÂŠ28502 apprenticesÂŠ28501 climbed into the boatÂŠ28498 and headed for the DalmanuthaÂŠ28514 region.
\s1 The religious leaders want to see a miracle
