\r (Mat. 16:1-4)
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 8:11: \xt Mat 12:38; Luk 11:16.\x*Some men from the Pharisee partyÂŠ28519 cameÂŠ28517 out to Yeshua and started arguing with him. They were checking him out and wanted to see a miracle.
\v 12 \x + \xo 8:12: \xt Mat 12:39; Luk 11:29.\x*Yeshua grieved inside andÂŠ28541 asked, â\wj Why do you people need to see a miracle before you'll believe me? Actually, no miracle will be done for this generation.\wj*â
\p
\v 13 SoÂŠ28568 Yeshua left in the boat againÂŠ28573 andÂŠ28568 crossed to the other side of the lake.
