\p
\v 14 ButÂŠ28582 Yeshua's apprentices forgotÂŠ28584 to takeÂŠ28588 any food other than one bun that someone in the boatÂŠ28604 had.
\v 15 \x + \xo 8:15: \xt Luk 12:1.\x*He told them, â\wj Watch out for the yeast of the Pharisees andÂŠ28618 of King HerodÂŠ28624.\wj*â
\p
\v 16 They asked each other what it meantâwas it becauseÂŠ28632 they forgot food?
\p
\v 17 ButÂŠ28638 \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were sayingÂŠ28642 andÂŠ28638 asked, â\wj Why are you all discussing about not having food? Can't you figure itÂŠ28639 out? Or are yourÂŠ28670 minds completely closed?\wj*
\v 18 \x + \xo 8:18: \xt Jer 5:21; Eze 12:2; Mrk 4:12.\x*\wj You all have eyesÂŠ28671 but can't seem to see andÂŠ28679 have earsÂŠ28680 but can't seem to listen. Have you already forgotten what just happened?\wj*
\v 19 \wj When I brokeÂŠ28700 up the five buns to feed five thousandÂŠ28703 people, how many basketfulsÂŠ28706 of leftovers did you collect?\wj*â
\p âTwelveÂŠ28714,â they answered.
\p
\v 20 âAnd when we fed fourÂŠ28723 thousandÂŠ28723 with sevenÂŠ28719 buns, how many full basketsÂŠ28726 of leftovers thenÂŠ28716?â
\p âSevenÂŠ28739,â theyÂŠ28737 answered.
\p
\v 21 Yeshua asked, â\wj How can you all not understandÂŠ28749 what's going on right in front of you!\wj*â
