\v 27 ThenÂŠ28889 \nd Yeshua\nd* andÂŠ28889 hisÂŠ28896 followers moved around the various villagesÂŠ28899 of Caesaria PhilippiÂŠ28903. On the way, he asked them, â\wj Who does everyoneÂŠ28921 think I am?\wj*â
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 8:28: \xt Mrk 6:14-15; Luk 9:7-8.\x*They said, âSome say Yohan-the-immerser, some say Eliyah, andÂŠ28935 some say one of the prophetsÂŠ28946.â
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 8:29: \xt Yhn 6:68-69.\x*ThenÂŠ28947 he asked, â\wj And what do you all think?\wj*â
\p PeterÂŠ28964 said, âYou are the promised one sent by God.â
\p
\v 30 ThenÂŠ28977 Yeshua warnedÂŠ28978 them not to tell others about himÂŠ28987.
\s1 Yeshua's radical challenge to his would-be followers
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks about His Suffering and Death; Jesus Predicts His Death
\r (Mat. 16:21-28; Luke 9:22-27)
\p
\v 31 ThenÂŠ28988 Yeshua beganÂŠ28991 teachingÂŠ28992 his followers that humanity's child would need to sufferÂŠ29001 a lot, to be rejectedÂŠ29003 by the religious leaders, andÂŠ28988 so to be put to death butÂŠ28988 to come back to life afterÂŠ29018 threeÂŠ29020 daysÂŠ29022.
\v 32 He taught this very clearly, butÂŠ29025 PeterÂŠ29034 took him asideÂŠ29031 andÂŠ29025 told him off.
\v 33 Yeshua turnedÂŠ29042 back andÂŠ29040 looked at the others, thenÂŠ29040 reprimanded PeterÂŠ29051, â\wj Stand back, SatanÂŠ29058! you'reÂŠ29061 applying humanÂŠ29068 values instead of considering God's plan.\wj*â
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 8:34: \xt Mat 10:38; Luk 14:27.\x*Calling out to them and to the crowdÂŠ29072, he saidÂŠ29077, â\wj Anyone who wants to follow me must first put aside their own desires and thenÂŠ29069 follow meâeven through very difficult times.\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 8:35: \xt Yhn 12:25; Mat 10:39; Luk 17:33.\x*\wj Anyone who worries about savingÂŠ29128 their own life will lose it, butÂŠ29124 anyone who gives their life due to following me and my teaching will save their life.\wj*
\v 36 \wj BecauseÂŠ29131 itÂŠ29133 doesn't benefitÂŠ29133 a personÂŠ29135 if they gain everything in the worldÂŠ29141 butÂŠ29144 lose their soulÂŠ29149.\wj*
\v 37 \wj What can someone offer in order to buy a home for their soulÂŠ29160?\wj*
\v 38 \wj Yes, anyone who is ashamed of me and myÂŠ29169 messageÂŠ29176 in front of this adulterousÂŠ29182 and sinfulÂŠ29184 generationÂŠ29179, humanity's child will likewise be ashamed of them when he comes clearly displaying God's greatness and bringing the holy messengersÂŠ29203.\wj*â
\c 9
\p
\v 1 And he continued, âI can assure you that some of the ones standing here won'tÂŠ29224 die untilÂŠ29227 they have seen God's powerfulÂŠ29236 kingdomÂŠ29231 arrive.â
\s1 Mosheh and Eliyah speak with Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Transfiguration
\r (Mat. 17:1-13; Luke 9:28-36)
\p
\v 2 \x + \xo 9:2-7: \xt 2Pe 1:17-18.\x*Six daysÂŠ29239 later \nd Yeshua\nd* took PeterÂŠ29246 and Yacob and Yohan, and just the four of them went up onto a highÂŠ29260 hillÂŠ29259. ThenÂŠ29237 he was changed right in front of their eyes
\v 3 andÂŠ29278 hisÂŠ29281 clothesÂŠ29280 turned incredibly shiningÂŠ29284 whiteâwhiter than any bleach could make them.
\v 4 And Eliyah and Mosheh appearedÂŠ29306 beside \nd Yeshua\nd* and started talking with him.
\v 5 PeterÂŠ29322 said to \nd Yeshua\nd*, âTeacher, it's goodÂŠ29329 that we're here. Maybe we could make threeÂŠ29341 shelters up here: one for youÂŠ29343 and one for Mosheh and one for Eliyah?â
