\p
\v 12 The next dayÂŠ31867 after they'd left Bethania, Yeshua was hungry.
\v 13 From a distance he noticed a figÂŠ31881 treeÂŠ31881 that was in leaf so he wentÂŠ31888 over to see if there was any fruit on it, butÂŠ31879 when he reached it there was only leaves becauseÂŠ31922 it wasn't the right seasonÂŠ31925 for figsÂŠ31929.
\v 14 SoÂŠ31930 he spoke to the tree, â\wj No one in this age will ever eatÂŠ31956 fruitÂŠ31954 from you again.\wj*â (HisÂŠ31963 followers heard him say that.)
\s1 Yeshua upsets the traders inside the temple
\rem /s1 Jesus Goes to the Temple; Jesus Cleanses the Temple; Jesus Clears the Temple
\r (Yhn 2:13-22; Mat. 21:12-17; Luke 19:45-48)
\p
\v 15 Then they came back into Yerushalem and on into the temple where Yeshua started drivingÂŠ31983 out the sellers and the buyers that were trading in there. Then he tipped over the tablesÂŠ31997 of the money-changers and the chairs of the ones selling dovesÂŠ32008,
\v 16 andÂŠ32012 stopped others from carryingÂŠ32017 goods through the templeÂŠ32024.
\v 17 \x + \xo 11:17: a \xt Isa 56:7; \xo b \xt Jer 7:11.\x*He said, â\wj Isn't it writtenÂŠ32032 in the Scriptures,\wj*
\q1 \wj âMyÂŠ32036 house will be known as a house of prayerÂŠ32038 for all the nationsÂŠ32042â?\wj*
\m \wj ButÂŠ32025 all of you have turned it into a sanctuary for swindlers.\wj*â
\p
\v 18 WhenÂŠ32052 the chiefÂŠ32055 priestsÂŠ32055 and the religiousÂŠ32059 teachersÂŠ32059 heardÂŠ32053 this, they started lookingÂŠ32062 forÂŠ32062 a way that they could destroyÂŠ32065 him, because they were afraid of him and the way that the crowdÂŠ32074 marvelled at hisÂŠ32080 teaching.
\p
\v 19 Every eveningÂŠ32084, Yeshua andÂŠ32081 his apprentices would go out of the cityÂŠ32092 to stay overnight.
\s1 Yeshua gives a lesson on moving mountains
\rem /s1 The Lesson from the Fig Tree; The Withered Fig Tree; The Lesson from the Withered Fig Tree
\r (Mat. 21:20-22)
\p
\v 20 As theyÂŠ32101 entered the city again in the morningÂŠ32099, Yeshua's apprentices noticedÂŠ32101 that the figÂŠ32103 treeÂŠ32103 was totally dead.
\v 21 PeterÂŠ32110 remembered what he had said to the tree, andÂŠ32107 commented, âTeacherÂŠ32113, that figÂŠ32117 tree that you cursedÂŠ32119 has witheredÂŠ32120 up.â
\p
\v 22 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, â\wj Use your faithÂŠ32130 in \+nd GodÂŠ32132\+nd*.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 11:23: \xt Mat 17:20; 1Cor 13:2.\x*\wj I can assure youÂŠ32136 that if anyone tells a mountainÂŠ32143 to go into the seaÂŠ32152 and doesn't doubtÂŠ32155 in their mindÂŠ32159 butÂŠ32147 believesÂŠ32163 that what they're sayingÂŠ32135 will happen, then itÂŠ32155 will.\wj*
\v 24 \wj So I tell you all that anything you ask God for in your prayers, if you believeÂŠ32192 that you have receivedÂŠ32194 itÂŠ32199, then you will.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 11:25-26: \xt Mat 6:14-15.\x*\wj Whenever you are standingÂŠ32205 prayingÂŠ32206, if you have something againstÂŠ32215 someone, be sure to forgive them so that your fatherÂŠ32220 in heavenÂŠ32226 can also forgive your shortcomings.\wj*â
\s1 The leaders question Yeshua's authority
\rem /s1 The Authority of Jesus Challenged; The Authority of Jesus Questioned; The Question about Jesus' Authority
\r (Mat. 21:23-27; Luke 20:1-8)
\p
\v 26 â
\rem /s1 Jesus' Authority Is Questioned
\v 27 They continued on into Yerushalem and on to the templeÂŠ32261 where theyÂŠ32253 were met by the chiefÂŠ32268 priestsÂŠ32268 and the religiousÂŠ32271 teachersÂŠ32271 and the eldersÂŠ32274.
\v 28 They asked Yeshua, âDo you have any authority to do what you did? If so, who gave it to you?â
\p
\v 29 \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, â\wj Okay, I'll also ask you something andÂŠ32301 when you answerÂŠ32316 me I'll tell you about my authorityÂŠ32326 to do that:\wj*
\v 30 \wj When Yohan \+add preached and\+add* immersedÂŠ32330 people, did the authority for thatÂŠ32331 come from heavenÂŠ32337 or from people here?\wj*â
\p
\v 31 They discussed this among themselvesÂŠ32351, reasoningÂŠ32347, âIf we sayÂŠ32357 it was from heavenÂŠ32359, he'll ask us why we didn'tÂŠ32367 believeÂŠ32368 himÂŠ32369.
\v 32 But weÂŠ32372 can't sayÂŠ32372 that it was just from people.â (They said that becauseÂŠ32383 they were scared of the crowdsÂŠ32379, knowing that they believed that Yohan was a prophetÂŠ32392.)
\v 33 SoÂŠ32394 theyÂŠ32399 answeredÂŠ32395, âWe don'tÂŠ32400 know.â
\p And \nd Yeshua\nd* also responded, â\wj Well thenÂŠ32394, I won'tÂŠ32400 tell youÂŠ32413 about my authorityÂŠ32418 to do those things either.\wj*â
\c 12
\s1 The parable about the tenants killing the owner's son
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Wicked Tenants; Story of the Evil Farmers; The Parable of the Tenants in the Vineyard
\r (Mat. 21:33-46; Luke 20:9-19)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 12:1: \xt Isa 5:1-2.\x*Then he started telling them some parablesÂŠ32426: â\wj A manÂŠ32431 plantedÂŠ32433 a vineyardÂŠ32429 and put a fenceÂŠ32438 and a moat aroundÂŠ32436 it and builtÂŠ32444 a \+add security\+add* towerÂŠ32445. Then he rentedÂŠ32447 it out and went off travellingÂŠ32452.\wj*
\v 2 \wj At harvest time, he sent a slaveÂŠ32460 to go to the tenant farmers andÂŠ32453 get his \+add percentage\+add* of the harvest.\wj*
\v 3 \wj ButÂŠ32484 the tenants grabbed the slave and beat him up, then sentÂŠ32485 him back empty-handed.\wj*
\v 4 \wj The owner sentÂŠ32491 a second slaveÂŠ32495, butÂŠ32489 theyÂŠ32500 insulted this one andÂŠ32489 struckÂŠ32500 him on the head.\wj*
\v 5 \wj SoÂŠ32506 the owner sent a third slave and they murdered him. He sent many other slavesâsome they just beat up and others they murdered.\wj*
\v 6 \wj But the owner stillÂŠ32527 had his one, dearly loved son, so finally he sentÂŠ32539 him to go, thinking that they would now be convinced because it was his son.\wj*
\v 7 \wj ButÂŠ32573 the tenantÂŠ32557 farmersÂŠ32557 saidÂŠ32564 to each others, âAh ha. This is the one who will inheritÂŠ32577 this land. If we killÂŠ32571 \+em himÂŠ32572\+em*, we'll be the ones to control the estate.â\wj*
\v 8 \wj SoÂŠ32578 they took him and killedÂŠ32581 him, and threw the body outsideÂŠ32586 the vineyardÂŠ32588 fence.\wj*
\p
\v 9 â\wj Now, what do you think the owner of the vineyard will do? Yes, he'll come and eliminate those \+add evil\+add* tenantsÂŠ32600, and give the contract to othersÂŠ32605.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 12:10-11: \xt Psa 118:22-23.\x*\wj Haven'tÂŠ32612 you all read this in the scripturesÂŠ32608:\wj*
\q1 \wj âthe stoneÂŠ32612 thatÂŠ32613 the buildersÂŠ32616 rejectedÂŠ32614\wj*
\q1 \wj became the \+add important\+add* cornerstoneÂŠ32621\wj*
\q1
\v 11 \wj that was given by \+nd YahwehÂŠ32623\+nd*,\wj*
\q1 \wj andÂŠ32626 we think it's incredible.â?\wj*â
\p
\v 12 And those leaders tried to arrest him because they knewÂŠ32640 that it was them that the parableÂŠ32646 was addressed to, butÂŠ32632 they couldn't do it because \add Yeshua had the favour\add* of the crowdÂŠ32639, so they just left the area.
\s1 Yeshua answers about payment of taxes
\rem /s1 Paying Taxes to Caesar; The Question about Paying Taxes; Taxes for Caesar
\r (Mat. 22:15-22; Luke 20:20-26)
\p
\v 13 ThenÂŠ32654 the religious leaders sent some members of the Pharisee partyÂŠ32660 andÂŠ32661 some of the \add political\add* supportersÂŠ32663 of King HerodÂŠ32663 to try to catchÂŠ32667 Yeshua out.
\v 14 SoÂŠ32670 they \add flattered\add* him, âTeacherÂŠ32683, we know that you are honest even if it upsets others, andÂŠ32670 that you teachÂŠ32707 the truthÂŠ32702 about \nd GodÂŠ32706\nd* without caringÂŠ32690 about people'sÂŠ32699 opinions. Is it legal \add for us Jews\add* to pay the poll taxÂŠ32717 to the Roman emperor or not? How should we handle this?â
\p
\v 15 ButÂŠ32728 knowingÂŠ32731 theirÂŠ32732 hypocrisyÂŠ32734, Yeshua respondedÂŠ32735 to them, â\wj Why are youÂŠ32739 trying to test me? Bring me a coin so we can determine the proper answer.\wj*â
\p
\v 16 WhenÂŠ32749 they broughtÂŠ32750 him a coin, he asked, â\wj Whose imageÂŠ32756 andÂŠ32749 inscriptionÂŠ32760 are on this coin?\wj*â
\p And they saidÂŠ32763, âThe emperor's.â
\p
\v 17 â\wj Well thenÂŠ32770,\wj*â said \nd Yeshua\nd*, â\wj give to the emperor whatever is due him, butÂŠ32770 give God what is owed to God.\wj*â
\p And they had to admit that that was an outstanding answer.
\s1 Yeshua explains that those who've died are alive
\rem /s1 The Question about Rising from Death; Discussion about Resurrection; The Question about the Resurrection; Marriage at the Resurrection
\r (Mat. 22:23-33; Luke 20:27-40)
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 12:18: \xt Acts 23:8.\x*Another time, members of the Sadducee sect came to Yeshua andÂŠ32806 asked,
\v 19 \x + \xo 12:19: \xt Deu 25:5.\x*âTeacherÂŠ32811, Mosheh wroteÂŠ32813 that if a man's married brother should die before his wife without having any childrenÂŠ32834, then his brother should marry her to produce descendants in his brother's name.
\v 20 Now what if there were sevenÂŠ32854 brothersÂŠ32856 and the firstÂŠ32863 one got married and died childless.
\v 21 So then the secondÂŠ32875 brother tookÂŠ32876 herÂŠ32877 in, butÂŠ32873 again diedÂŠ32879 childless, and then the thirdÂŠ32890.
\v 22 Eventually all sevenÂŠ32899 brothers died childless, and finally the womanÂŠ32911 also died.
\v 23 Now, at the resurrectionÂŠ32916 of the dead, whichÂŠ32920 brother will she be the wife of, becauseÂŠ32927 at some point, she was married to each of the sevenÂŠ32928 of them?â
\p
\v 24 So \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, â\wj Actually you're all quite wrong, because you ignore the scripturesÂŠ32949 and also because you haven't experienced God's powerÂŠ32952.\wj*
\v 25 \wj When the deadÂŠ32959 do come back to life, they won't be getting engaged or married, but will be like the messengersÂŠ32974 in heavenÂŠ32978.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 12:26: \xt Exo 3:6.\x*\wj And as for the state of those who've died, didn'tÂŠ32986 you read in the scriptures about Mosheh when \nd GodÂŠ33004\nd* spokeÂŠ33001 to him in front of the \+add burning\+add* thornÂŠ32997 bush and said, âI \+em am\+em* the god of AbrahamÂŠ33010 and the god of IsaacÂŠ33014 and the god of YacobÂŠ33018â?\wj*
\v 27 \wj So \nd GodÂŠ33022\nd* is not the \nd godÂŠ33022\nd* of the deadÂŠ33023, butÂŠ33024 of the livingÂŠ33026. You Sadducees are very wrong!\wj*â
\s1 Yeshua answers about genuine obedience to God
\rem /s1 The Most Important Commandment; The Great Commandment; The Greatest Commandment; The First Commandment
\r (Mat. 22:34-40; Luke 10:25-28)
\p
\v 28 ThenÂŠ33031 one of the religiousÂŠ33036 teachersÂŠ33036 who had heardÂŠ33037 theirÂŠ33039 question and Yeshua's excellent answerÂŠ33048, came closer and askedÂŠ33050, âWhichÂŠ33054 of \+add God's\+add* commandsÂŠ33056 is the most important?â
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 12:29-30: \xt Deu 6:4-5.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* answeredÂŠ33064, â\wj Well, the most important is this: âListen, Yisrael. OurÂŠ33086 \+nd \nd GodÂŠ33085\nd* YahwehÂŠ33083\+nd* is \add &our\add* master.\wj*
\v 30 \wj You must love \+nd \nd YahwehÂŠ33092\nd* GodÂŠ33094\+nd* with all your heartÂŠ33099 and with all your soulÂŠ33106 and with all your mindÂŠ33099 and with all your strengthÂŠ33119.â\wj*
\v 31 \x + \xo 12:31: \xt Lev 19:18.\x*\wj And the secondÂŠ33125 is: âLove yourÂŠ33136 neighbourÂŠ33135 like \+add youÂŠ33136 look after\+add* yourselfÂŠ33138.â There's no other commandsÂŠ33143 more important than theseÂŠ33141.\wj*â
\p
\v 32 \x + \xo 12:32: \xt Deu 4:35.\x*The teacher replied to Yeshua, âYes, teacher, you're quite right saying there'sÂŠ33167 only one God andÂŠ33165 no other,
\v 33 \x + \xo 12:33: \xt Hos 6:6.\x*and saying thatÂŠ33199 we should love him with all our heartÂŠ33178 and all our intelligenceÂŠ33186 and all our strengthÂŠ33197, and to be loving our neighboursÂŠ33202 like we \add look after\add* ourselves, and all this is more importantÂŠ33207 than all the required temple offeringsÂŠ33212 and sacrificesÂŠ33215.â
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 12:28-34: \xt Luk 10:25-28.\x*WhenÂŠ33216 Yeshua saw that he'd given such a thoughtful answerÂŠ33223, he saidÂŠ33224, â\wj You're very close to \+nd GodÂŠ33234's\+nd* kingdomÂŠ33232!\wj*â
\p After that, no one else dared to askÂŠ33241 Yeshua any more questions.
\s1 Yeshua asks about the messiah being David's descendant
\rem /s1 Whose Son Is the Messiah?; The Question about the Messiah; Whose Son Is the Christ; The Question about David's Son
\r (Mat. 22:41-46; Luke 20:41-44)
\p
\v 35 Later when \nd Yeshua\nd* was teaching in the templeÂŠ33253, he asked the people, â\wj How is it that the teachersÂŠ33258 here say that the \+nd messiahÂŠ33261\+nd* is a descendant of King DavidÂŠ33264?\wj*
\v 36 \x + \xo 12:36: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*\wj Because David himselfÂŠ33267 said under the inspiration of the holy \+nd spiritÂŠ33274\+nd*,\wj*
\q1 \wj âThe \+nd master\+nd* told myÂŠ33283 \+nd master\+nd*,\wj*
\q2 \wj âSit there in the position of honour\wj*
\q2 \wj untilÂŠ33289 I can conquer yourÂŠ33295 enemiesÂŠ33294.â â\wj*
\m
\v 37 \wj If David calls \add @the messiah\add* hisÂŠ33311 \+nd masterÂŠ33306\+nd*, how can \add @the messiah\add* possibly be \add @David's\add* descendant?\wj*â
\p The large crowdÂŠ33318 was very interested to hearÂŠ33320 everything that Yeshua had to say.
\s1 Yeshua warns about well-dressed teachers
\rem /s1 Jesus Warns against the Teachers of the Law; Jesus Denounces the Scribes
\r (Mat. 23:1-36; Luke 20:45-47)
\p
\v 38 As Yeshua continued teaching, he said, â\wj Watch out for these religiousÂŠ33341 teachersÂŠ33341 who like to wear \+add fancy\+add* robesÂŠ33348 andÂŠ33328 be greetedÂŠ33351 in the square,\wj*
\v 39 \wj and have the best seatsÂŠ33357 at meetings and the best placesÂŠ33362 at dinners.\wj*
\v 40 \wj TheseÂŠ33380 people trick widowsÂŠ33372 out of their properties, butÂŠ33373 offer longÂŠ33377 prayers to cover it up. They will be getting a stricter judgementÂŠ33384 than others.\wj*â
\s1 The sacrificial donation of a widow
\rem /s1 The Widow's Offering
\r (Luke 21:1-4)
\p
\v 41 As he satÂŠ33386 down in frontÂŠ33390 of the \add temple\add* treasury, Yeshua watched the crowdÂŠ33402 as they threw coins into \add the dish\add*, andÂŠ33385 some rich people were donating quite valuable \add silver\add* coins.
\v 42 ThenÂŠ33415 an impoverished widowÂŠ33421 came andÂŠ33415 threw in twoÂŠ33425 small \add copper\add* coins.
\v 43 Yeshua calledÂŠ33430 hisÂŠ33433 followers andÂŠ33429 told them, â\wj Honestly, that poor widowÂŠ33442 gave more than all the others.\wj*
\v 44 \wj You see, most people donate from their excess wealthÂŠ33463, butÂŠ33470 this womanÂŠ33469 even gave \+add some of\+add* the small amount that sheÂŠ33477 needed to live on.\wj*â
\c 13
\s1 Yeshua predicts total destruction of the temple
\rem /s1 Warnings about the end; Jesus Speaks of the Destruction of the Temple; The Destruction of the Temple Foretold; Signs of the End of the Age; Jesus Foretells the Future
\r (Mat. 24:1-2; Luke 21:5-6)
\p
\v 1 As they were leaving the templeÂŠ33488 area, one of Yeshua's followers noted, âTeacherÂŠ33498, look at those \add large, chiselled\add* stonesÂŠ33501 andÂŠ33502 the \add beautiful\add* buildingsÂŠ33504 \add that they've been made into\add*.â
\p
\v 2 ButÂŠ33507 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedÂŠ33512, â\wj Yes, incredible buildingsÂŠ33522, butÂŠ33507 \+add the time will come\+add* when they're torn downânot a single \+add piece of\+add* stoneÂŠ33533 will be left sitting in its place.\wj*â
\s1 Yeshua talks about coming hardships
\rem /s1 Troubles and Persecutions
\r (Mat. 24:3-14; Luke 21:7-19)
\p
\v 3 Later when they were over on the MountÂŠ33557 of OlivesÂŠ33559 overlooking the templeÂŠ33562, PeterÂŠ33569 and Yacob and Yohan and AndrewÂŠ33575 were with Yeshua and asked
\v 4 when all this destruction would happen, andÂŠ33581 what indications there would be that it would be about to happen.
\p
\v 5 SoÂŠ33597 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, â\wj Be careful so youÂŠ33609 aren't misledÂŠ33610 by others.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Plenty of people will say that they're comingÂŠ33614 \+add âbecause they were sent by me\+add*, or that they \+em are\+em* me, and they'll misleadÂŠ33628 many others.\wj*
\v 7 \wj And wheneverÂŠ33629 youÂŠ33631 hearÂŠ33631 about wars or about battles about to begin, don'tÂŠ33638 be worriedâthose things will certainly happen, butÂŠ33643 there's more to follow.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Countries will take up arms against other countries, and kingdoms against other kingdoms. There'llÂŠ33657 be earthquakesÂŠ33658 in \+add many\+add* placesÂŠ33660 and there'llÂŠ33662 be faminesÂŠ33663, butÂŠ33652 those will be just like the beginningÂŠ33667 of birthÂŠ33668 painsÂŠ33668.\wj*
\rem /s1 Persecution Foretold
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 13:9-11: \xt Mat 10:17-20; Luk 12:11-12.\x*â\wj So be careful. You'll be turned over to \+add local\+add* councilsÂŠ33683 \+add for questioning\+add*, will be whipped in the religious meetingÂŠ33686 hallsÂŠ33686, and will be stoodÂŠ33696 in front of governorsÂŠ33691 and kingsÂŠ33695 becauseÂŠ33701 of following me. ButÂŠ33684 you'll be able to present your life stories to them\wj*
\v 10 \wj andÂŠ33704 it's right that the goodÂŠ33718 news first\f + \fr 13:10 \ft TD: It's not clear here what was meant by âfirstâââfirstâ before what?\f* be proclaimedÂŠ33716 to every people group.\wj*
\v 11 \wj But wheneverÂŠ33724 they bringÂŠ33726 you along to hand you over, don'tÂŠ33730 worryÂŠ33731 in advance about what you're going to say to defend yourselves, but wait until the hearing proceeds and speak what you are givenÂŠ33740 then, becauseÂŠ33752 then it won'tÂŠ33730 be you speaking, but God's \+nd spiritÂŠ33759\+nd*.\wj*
\v 12 \wj In those times, a brother will report on his brother to have him executed, and a fatherÂŠ33770 report on his child, and children will be encouraged to report on their own parentsÂŠ33778 and thenÂŠ33762 they'll be executed as a result.\wj*
\v 13 \x + \xo 13:13: \xt Mat 10:22.\x*\wj And every one will hate youÂŠ33783 all becauseÂŠ33787 they hate myÂŠ33790 nameÂŠ33789, butÂŠ33792 anyone who enduresÂŠ33793 to the endÂŠ33795 will be savedÂŠ33797.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua warns about coming horror and deceptions
\rem /s1 The Desolating Sacrilege; The Awful Horror
\r (Mat. 24:15-28; Luke 21:20-24)
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 13:14: \xt Dan 9:27; 11:31; 12:11.\x*â\wj But wheneverÂŠ33798 you seeÂŠ33801 the most horrible thing that drives people from God, standing whereÂŠ33817 itÂŠ33819 shouldn'tÂŠ33818 be (and you readers should understandÂŠ33822 this), then anyone in YudeaÂŠ33829 should flee into the hills\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 13:15-16: \xt Luk 17:31.\x*\wj and anyone upstairs looking outside shouldn'tÂŠ33840 come down into the bedrooms to get anythingÂŠ33849,\wj*
\v 16 \wj andÂŠ33855 anyone working outside shouldn'tÂŠ33861 go back inside to get a change of clothes.\wj*
\v 17 \wj It will be extremely difficult for pregnant women and for mothers who are breast-feeding their childrenÂŠ33877 in thoseÂŠ33883 daysÂŠ33885.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Just pray that itÂŠ33891 won'tÂŠ33890 happen in the winterÂŠ33895\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 13:19: \xt Dan 12:1; Rev 7:14.\x*\wj becauseÂŠ33898 thoseÂŠ33901 daysÂŠ33900 will be terrible like nothing that's ever happened before, all the way back to when \+nd GodÂŠ33918\+nd* createdÂŠ33913 the world right untilÂŠ33919 the present timeÂŠ33920, andÂŠ33923 won'tÂŠ33906 ever happen again.\wj*
\v 20 \wj And if \+nd YahwehÂŠ33933\+nd* hadn't shortened that time, no humans wouldÂŠ33941 even survive, butÂŠ33945 he shortened that time so that the chosenÂŠ33949 ones could be savedÂŠ33942.\wj*
\p
\v 21 \wj SoÂŠ33956 don'tÂŠ33974 believeÂŠ33975 itÂŠ33975 if youÂŠ33961 hear someone sayÂŠ33962, âLookÂŠ33964, the \+nd messiahÂŠ33968\+nd* has arrived here.â or âThere's the one that God has sent.â\wj*
\v 22 \wj Plenty of fake messiahsÂŠ33981 and deceiving prophetsÂŠ33983 will certainly come and even do things that humans can't normally do, so much so that even the chosenÂŠ33998 ones would defect if that were possibleÂŠ33995.\wj*
\v 23 \wj So watchÂŠ34001 out, butÂŠ34000 I'veÂŠ34003 warned you in advance about all of this.\wj*
\s1 The universe collapses as the son arrives
\rem /s1 The Coming of the Son of Man
\r (Mat. 24:29-31; Luke 21:25-28)
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 13:24: a \xt Isa 13:10; Yoel 2:10,31; 3:15; Rev 6:12; \xo b \xt Isa 13:10; Eze 32:7.\x*â\wj After thoseÂŠ34009 very difficult times, the sunÂŠ34017 will go dark andÂŠ34019 the moonÂŠ34021 won'tÂŠ34022 shine at night.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 13:25: a \xt Isa 34:4; Rev 6:13; \xo b \xt Yoel 2:10.\x*\wj The starsÂŠ34029 will fall down out of the skyÂŠ34034 and the powersÂŠ34041 in the heavensÂŠ34047 will be shakenÂŠ34050 up.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 13:26: \xt Dan 7:13; Rev 1:7.\x*\wj ThenÂŠ34051 the people will see humanity's child in the cloudsÂŠ34062 comingÂŠ34058 with incredible powerÂŠ34066 andÂŠ34068 brightness.\wj*
\v 27 \wj He'll send the messengersÂŠ34076 out to collect all the chosenÂŠ34082 people from the fourÂŠ34086 corners of the world, from everywhere between the earthÂŠ34092 andÂŠ34078 the sky.\wj*
\s1 Watch out for the change in season
\rem /s1 The Lesson of the Fig Tree
\r (Mat. 24:32-35; Luke 21:29-33)
\p
\v 28 â\wj SoÂŠ34099 learnÂŠ34102 a lesson from figÂŠ34101 treesâwheneverÂŠ34105 the branchesÂŠ34109 green up and start sproutingÂŠ34114 leavesÂŠ34116 and thenÂŠ34099 everyone knows that summerÂŠ34125 is close.\wj*
\v 29 \wj So too wheneverÂŠ34130 you seeÂŠ34132 all theseÂŠ34134 things happening, you know that the end \+add of this current world\+add* is close.\wj*
\v 30 \wj I can assure you that the generationÂŠ34155 of people who see these things won'tÂŠ34152 die off before these latter things happen.\wj*
\v 31 \wj The sky andÂŠ34167 the planet might collapse, butÂŠ34173 myÂŠ34175 teachings will never become irrelevant.\wj*
\s1 Stay alert for the coming of the master
\rem /s1 The Day and Hour Unknown; The Necessity for Watchfulness; No One Knows the Day or Hour
\r (Mat. 24:36-44)
\p
\v 32 \x + \xo 13:32: \xt Mat 24:36.\x*â\wj But as for the date or time when all this will happen, only the fatherÂŠ34205 knows thatâeven the son and messengersÂŠ34193 don'tÂŠ34191 know.\wj*
\v 33 \wj So watch out, observe current events, andÂŠ34210 be prayingÂŠ34211, becauseÂŠ34214 youÂŠ34213 won'tÂŠ34212 know exactly when all this will happen.\wj*
\v 34 \x + \xo 13:34: \xt Luk 12:36-38.\x*\wj It can all be compared to a manÂŠ34229 who was about to leave his houseÂŠ34234 and go on a trip. Before he leaves, he gives certain jobs and responsibilities to his various slavesÂŠ34240, and instructs his security guard to stay alert.\wj*
\v 35 \wj SoÂŠ34257 you all watchÂŠ34256 and stay alert, becauseÂŠ34260 you don'tÂŠ34258 know when the masterÂŠ34263 of the houseÂŠ34265 might returnâperhaps one eveningÂŠ34268 or at midnightÂŠ34271, or at dawn or maybe mid-morning.\wj*
\v 36 \wj You certainly don't want to be caught napping when heÂŠ34280 comes.\wj*
\v 37 \wj And what I'm telling youÂŠ34287 now, I tell everyone: stay alert andÂŠ34286 watchÂŠ34292.\wj*â
\c 14
\s1 The leaders plan to eliminate Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Plot against Jesus; The trial and crucifixion of Jesus; Jesus Anointed at Bethany; The Plot to Kill Jesus
\r (Yhn 11:45-53; Mat. 26:1-5; Luke 22:1-2)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 14:1: \xt Exo 12:1-27.\x*Now it was twoÂŠ34301 daysÂŠ34302 before the Passover Feast and the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it*, and the chiefÂŠ34306 priestsÂŠ34306 and the religiousÂŠ34310 teachersÂŠ34310 were trying to figure out how they could have Yeshua set up so they could arrest him and have him executed,
\v 2 but theyÂŠ34319 knew that the Feast wouldn't be a good time becauseÂŠ34320 the peopleÂŠ34332 would protest \add in Yeshua's favour\add*.
\s1 The woman anoints Yeshua for his burial
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany; The Anointing at Bethany
\r (Yhn 12:1-8; Mat. 26:6-13)
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 14:3: \xt Luk 7:37-38.\x*Meanwhile, Yeshua was in BethanyÂŠ34339 at the home of SimonÂŠ34343 who had previously had leprosyÂŠ34345. Yeshua was sittingÂŠ34346 there when a womanÂŠ34349 cameÂŠ34348 in with a hand-crafted container of very expensiveÂŠ34357 fragrant oil. Breaking open the sealed flask, sheÂŠ34367 pouredÂŠ34367 the fragrant oil over Yeshua's head.
\v 4 Immediately some started quietly grumbling about the extravagant waste,
\v 5 thenÂŠ34414 theyÂŠ34415 scolded the woman becauseÂŠ34399 a flask of genuine lotion like this could easily fetch almost a year's wages if it was sold.
\p
\v 6 But \nd Yeshua\nd* spoke up, â\wj What do you think you're doing abusing herâleave her alone! She'sÂŠ34433 done something very goodÂŠ34430 for me.\wj*
\v 7 \x + \xo 14:7: \xt Deu 15:11.\x*\wj You'll always have poor people around, and you can help them wheneverÂŠ34447 you want to, butÂŠ34446 I won'tÂŠ34458 be around forever.\wj*
\v 8 \wj She has performed the traditional anointingÂŠ34468 of my bodyÂŠ34471 in advance of my burialÂŠ34475.\wj*
\v 9 \wj And I can assure youÂŠ34479 that whereverÂŠ34481 the goodÂŠ34486 news is proclaimedÂŠ34484 around the worldÂŠ34491, what she has done today will be part of the story andÂŠ34477 she'll be remembered for it.\wj*â
\s1 Yudas offers to hand Yeshua over
\rem /s1 Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:14-16; Luke 22:3-6)
\p
\v 10 ThenÂŠ34500 YudasÂŠ34503 IscariotÂŠ34505, one of Yeshua's twelveÂŠ34510 \add apprentices\add*, visited the chiefÂŠ34514 priestsÂŠ34514 to offer to hand Yeshua over to them.
\v 11 WhenÂŠ34523 they heardÂŠ34524 this, they were very pleased and promisedÂŠ34528 to pay him well, and Yudas asked them about the most convenientÂŠ34538 way for them to get hold of Yeshua.
\s1 Yeshua's apprentices prepare the Passover meal
\rem /s1 The Lord's Supper; The Last Supper; The Passover with the Disciples; Jesus Eats the Passover Meal with His Disciples; Communion
\r (Yhn 13:21-30; Mat. 26:17-25; Luke 22:7-14, 21-23)
\p
\v 12 On the firstÂŠ34542 dayÂŠ34543 of the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it* when the lambs would be slaughtered ready for the special Passover meal, Yeshua's apprenticesÂŠ34553 asked him, âWhereÂŠ34555 do you want us to get everything ready for our Passover meal?â
\p
\v 13 SoÂŠ34564 Yeshua sent off twoÂŠ34567 of them with these instructions, â\wj Go into townÂŠ34582 andÂŠ34564 a manÂŠ34588 carrying a pitcherÂŠ34589 of waterÂŠ34590 will meet you there. Just followÂŠ34592 him\wj*
\v 14 \wj until he goes into a house. ThenÂŠ34594 find the ownerÂŠ34601 of the house and tell him that the teacherÂŠ34604 wants to know the location of the guestroomÂŠ34609 whereÂŠ34595 he and his apprenticesÂŠ34616 can celebrate the Passover meal.\wj*
\v 15 \wj He'll show you a largeÂŠ34628, furnishedÂŠ34629 roomÂŠ34626 upstairsÂŠ34626âthat's where you can get everything readyÂŠ34631.\wj*â
\p
\v 16 SoÂŠ34637 the two of them wentÂŠ34638 off into the townÂŠ34652, and everything happened there exactly as Yeshua had told them, and so they preparedÂŠ34660 the special meal there.
\s1 Yeshua shocks his apprentices at the Passover meal
\r (Yhn 13:21-30; Mat. 26:20-30; Luke 22:14-23; 1 Cor. 11:23-25)
\p
\v 17 As the eveningÂŠ34664 approached, Yeshua went in for dinner with his twelveÂŠ34671 apprentices.
\v 18 \x + \xo 14:18: \xt Psa 41:9.\x*As they were sittingÂŠ34673 around eating, he told them, â\wj I'll tell you frankly that one of you eating with me here will hand me over \+add to be arrested\+add*.\wj*â
\v 19 That upset them, andÂŠ34703 several of them individually asked, âSurelyÂŠ34710 it couldn't be me?â
\p
\v 20 ThenÂŠ34719 he continuedÂŠ34721, â\wj It's one of you twelveÂŠ34727âthe one who dips his bread in the sauce at the same time as me.\wj*
\v 21 \wj Indeed it's writtenÂŠ34749 \+add in the scriptures\+add* that humanity's child will be arrested, but on the otherÂŠ34754 hand, what a tragedy it'll be for the one who hands him overâin fact it would be betterÂŠ34765 for that man if he was never born.\wj*â
\rem /s1 The Lord's Supper; The Institution of the Lord's Supper; Communion
\rem /r (Matthew 26.26-30; Luke 22.14-20; 1 Corinthians 11.23-25)
\p
\v 22 As they carried on eatingÂŠ34776, he took some bread, blessedÂŠ34782 \add God\add*, brokeÂŠ34785 it apart andÂŠ34775 gave a piece to them, saying, â\wj Take this breadâit's myÂŠ34800 bodyÂŠ34799.\wj*â
\p
\v 23 ThenÂŠ34801 he picked up a cup, gaveÂŠ34806 thanksÂŠ34805 \add to God\add*, andÂŠ34801 passed it around so they could each drink from it,
\v 24 \x + \xo 14:24: a \xt Exo 24:8; \xo b \xt Jer 31:31-34.\x*saying, â\wj This is the bloodÂŠ34821 of myÂŠ34822 contract thatÂŠ34827 will be pouredÂŠ34831 out for many \+add people\+add*.\wj*
\v 25 \wj I can assure you that I won'tÂŠ34843 drink anything made from grapes untilÂŠ34852 I drink new juice in God's kingdomÂŠ34862.\wj*â
\rem /s1 Peter's Denial Foretold
\p
\v 26 And after they'd sung some songs, they leftÂŠ34867 the town andÂŠ34865 wentÂŠ34867 across to the MountÂŠ34870 of OlivesÂŠ34872.
\s1 Yeshua predicts Peters denials
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial
\r (Yhn 13:36-38; Mat. 26:31-35; Luke 22:31-34)
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 14:27: \xt Zech 13:7.\x*ThenÂŠ34874 \nd Yeshua\nd* continued his teaching, â\wj All of youÂŠ34882 will stumbleÂŠ34882 becauseÂŠ34891 it's writtenÂŠ34892 in the scriptures: âI'llÂŠ34893 strikeÂŠ34893 down the shepherdÂŠ34895 andÂŠ34896 the sheepÂŠ34900 will be scatteredÂŠ34902.â\wj*
\v 28 \x + \xo 14:28: \xt Mat 28:16.\x*\wj But afterÂŠ34905 I come back to life, I'llÂŠ34911 go on ahead of youÂŠ34912 back to GalileeÂŠ34915.\wj*â
\p
\v 29 ButÂŠ34917 PeterÂŠ34918 contradicted himÂŠ34922, âEven if everyone else stumblesÂŠ34928, I won'tÂŠ34931!â
\p
\v 30 And \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, â\wj I can assure you that you'll renounceÂŠ34961 me threeÂŠ34957 times this very nightÂŠ34949, beforeÂŠ34951 the roosterÂŠ34954 crows early tomorrow morning.\wj*â
\p
\v 31 ButÂŠ34989 Peter argued forcibly, âEven if I had to dieÂŠ34980 with you, I would never disown you!â
\p And all the others said similar things.
\s1 Yeshua, in distress, prays at Gethsemane
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays in Gethsemane
\r (Mat. 26:36-46; Luke 22:39-46)
\p
\v 32 They walked along untilÂŠ35011 they came to a piece of land called GethsemaneÂŠ35002 where Yeshua told hisÂŠ35008 apprenticesÂŠ35007 to sit down while he prayed.
\v 33 He took PeterÂŠ35017 and Yacob and Yohan further in with him where he stared off in a daze butÂŠ35014 was obviously very distressedÂŠ35031.
\v 34 He told the three of them, â\wj MyÂŠ35040 soulÂŠ35039 is deathlyÂŠ35042 sad! You guys just stay here andÂŠ35045 keep alert.\wj*â
\p
\v 35 He went ahead a littleÂŠ35050 way, where he knelt on the groundÂŠ35058 with his head down andÂŠ35047 prayedÂŠ35061âasking if it was possibleÂŠ35064 to avoid what was ahead of him.
\v 36 ButÂŠ35074 he said, â\wj Father, I know that you can do anything. Let me avoid this suffering, but yes I do know, it doesn't matter what I wantÂŠ35105 but rather what you've \+add planned\+add*.\wj*â
\p
\v 37 ThenÂŠ35107 he went back andÂŠ35107 found the others sleeping. He asked PeterÂŠ35116, â\wj SimonÂŠ35117, are you asleep? Couldn't you stay awake even for a single hourÂŠ35123?\wj*
\v 38 \wj You all need to stay alert and be careful not to give into temptationÂŠ35133. I know your spiritsÂŠ35136 are enthusiastic on one hand, butÂŠ35126 it's still easy to give in to the moment.\wj*â
\p
\v 39 ThenÂŠ35142 he went further in again andÂŠ35142 prayedÂŠ35145 as before,
\v 40 but when he returned againÂŠ35151, he foundÂŠ35154 them all asleep becauseÂŠ35159 they were tired, but they couldn't really find any excuse to give.
\p
\v 41 The thirdÂŠ35178 time that Yeshua returned, he said to them, â\wj Ah, you're all sleepingÂŠ35182 again andÂŠ35175 having a good rest. It's well earned butÂŠ35175 the time has come for humanity's child to be handed over to evil men.\wj*
\v 42 \wj Come onâget upâweÂŠ35208 need to go! LookÂŠ35209, the one who'll hand me over is on his way.\wj*â
\s1 Yeshua is arrested in the night
\rem /s1 Jesus Arrested; Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested; The Arrest of Jesus; The Betrayal and Arrest of Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:3-12; Mat. 26:47-56; Luke 22:47-53)
\p
\v 43 Even while Yeshua was stillÂŠ35219 speakingÂŠ35221, YudasÂŠ35224 reached him, followed by a crowdÂŠ35234 from the chiefÂŠ35243 priestsÂŠ35243, the religiousÂŠ35247 teachersÂŠ35247, and the eldersÂŠ35250âmany armed with swordsÂŠ35237 and clubsÂŠ35239.
\v 44 Yudas had prearranged a signalÂŠ35258 with them that anyone who he greeted with a kissÂŠ35264, they should grab that person andÂŠ35253 lead him away under guard.
\p
\v 45 SoÂŠ35275 he walked right up to Yeshua and said, âMy honoured teacher,â and greeted him with a kiss.
\v 46 ThenÂŠ35290 the others with him grabbed Yeshua andÂŠ35290 secured him.
\v 47 ButÂŠ35321 one of the ones with Yeshua that was beside himÂŠ35323, drew hisÂŠ35323 swordÂŠ35312 andÂŠ35321 struckÂŠ35315 a slaveÂŠ35318 of the chiefÂŠ35320 priestÂŠ35320, cutting off the man's earÂŠ35325.
\v 48 \nd Yeshua\nd* spoke to the crowd, â\wj Did you all bring swordsÂŠ35338 andÂŠ35339 clubsÂŠ35340 to try to captureÂŠ35341 me like you'd chase down a thief?\wj*
\v 49 \x + \xo 14:49: \xt Luk 19:47; 21:37.\x*\wj I was standing there teachingÂŠ35351 in the templeÂŠ35350 everyÂŠ35343 dayÂŠ35344 and you could have arrested me, butÂŠ35352 it's happened this way to ensure that the what's written in scripturesÂŠ35361 will be fulfilledÂŠ35359.\wj*â
\p
\v 50 Meanwhile, the others who'd been with Yeshua had taken off.
\v 51 One youngÂŠ35377 fellow was wearing a single linenÂŠ35386 robe, andÂŠ35374 when the crowd tried to grab him,
\v 52 it came off \add in the struggle\add* and he ran away stark nakedÂŠ35404.
\s1 The mock trial where Yeshua is sentenced to death
\rem /s1 Jesus before the Council; Before the Sanhedrin
\r (Yhn 18:13-14,19-24; Mat. 26:57-68; Luke 22:54-55,63-71)
\p
\v 53 The guards led \nd Yeshua\nd* away to the chief priest's residence, and all the chief priestsÂŠ35424 and the eldersÂŠ35429 and the religiousÂŠ35433 teachersÂŠ35433 gathered there also.
\v 54 PeterÂŠ35436 followedÂŠ35439 along from a distance andÂŠ35434 went in as far as the courtyardÂŠ35446 of the residence where he joined the servants who were sittingÂŠ35452 around the fireÂŠ35461 keeping warm.
\v 55 Inside, the chiefÂŠ35464 priestsÂŠ35464 andÂŠ35463 all the councilÂŠ35468 were trying to establish a case againstÂŠ35470 \nd Yeshua\nd* so he could be sentenced to deathÂŠ35478, butÂŠ35463 they weren't coming up with anything.
\v 56 Several people were making up charges againstÂŠ35488 himÂŠ35489, butÂŠ35490 none of the accusers' stories agreed with each other.
\p
\v 57 Eventually some of them stoodÂŠ35499 up andÂŠ35496 offered this falseÂŠ35500 charge:
\v 58 \x + \xo 14:58: \xt Yhn 2:19.\x*âWe heardÂŠ35508 him say that he would demolish this templeÂŠ35517 made by many labourers, and within threeÂŠ35523 daysÂŠ35524 he'd buildÂŠ35528 anotherÂŠ35525 one without any helpers.â
\v 59 ButÂŠ35529 even thenÂŠ35529, they couldn't get theirÂŠ35537 accusations to align with each other.
\p
\v 60 Nevertheless the chiefÂŠ35541 priestÂŠ35541 in the middle of the council stoodÂŠ35539 up andÂŠ35538 askedÂŠ35545 \nd Yeshua\nd*, âAren't you going to defend yourself? These menÂŠ35554 are accusing you of theseÂŠ35554 things.â
\p
\v 61 ButÂŠ35564 Yeshua didn'tÂŠ35565 say anything. So the chiefÂŠ35573 priestÂŠ35573 asked again, âIs it true that you're the \nd chosenÂŠ35587\nd* one that God promised to sendâthe son of the blessedÂŠ35593 \add God\add*?â
\p
\v 62 \x + \xo 14:62: \xt Dan 7:13.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* replied, âI am. And youÂŠ35605 will all see humanity's child sittingÂŠ35613 in the honoured position by the powerfulÂŠ35615 God andÂŠ35616 comingÂŠ35617 through the cloudsÂŠ35621 in the skyÂŠ35624.â
\p
\v 63 ThenÂŠ35626 the chiefÂŠ35627 priestÂŠ35627 tore his own robe \add to show his disgust\add* andÂŠ35626 shouted, âWe certainly don't need any more witnessesÂŠ35639 now!
\v 64 \x + \xo 14:64: \xt Lev 24:16.\x*You yourselves all heardÂŠ35642 himÂŠ35662 insult God. What sentence does that deserve?â
\p SoÂŠ35658 the leaders there agreed that Yeshua needed to be sentenced to deathÂŠ35667.
\p
\v 65 ThenÂŠ35668 various people started spittingÂŠ35671 on him, and blindfoldingÂŠ35674 him and beatingÂŠ35682 him sayingÂŠ35686, âHa, tell us who that was!â Even the servants joined in to slap him.
\s1 Peter disowns Yeshua
\rem /s1 Peter Denies Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:15-18,25-27; Mat. 26:69-75; Luke 22:56-62)
\p
\v 66 Meanwhile, PeterÂŠ35709 was down in the courtyardÂŠ35713 when one of the chiefÂŠ35723 priest'sÂŠ35723 servantÂŠ35720 girlsÂŠ35720 came out,
\v 67 and seeing PeterÂŠ35727 warmingÂŠ35728 himselfÂŠ35728, sheÂŠ35732 looked more closely and said, âHey, you were with that \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethÂŠ35740\nd*!â
\p
\v 68 ButÂŠ35760 he denied it, âI don't know him andÂŠ35760 I don't know why you think I would!â And he moved away from the fire.
\p
\v 69 ButÂŠ35775 the girlÂŠ35777 that had seenÂŠ35778 himÂŠ35779 said to some of the others standing around, âThat guy's one of them.â
\p
\v 70 ButÂŠ35805 again PeterÂŠ35814 denied it.
\p A littleÂŠ35807 while later, some of those standing there said, âYou must be one of them becauseÂŠ35820 you'reÂŠ35818 from GalileeÂŠ35821.â
\p
\v 71 Now Peter started swearingÂŠ35834 and cursingÂŠ35831 and said, âI'veÂŠ35837 never even met that fellow that you're all talkingÂŠ35842 about!â
\p
\v 72 Right thenÂŠ35843 the rooster crowed for the secondÂŠ35846 timeÂŠ35846 and PeterÂŠ35853 remembered now what Yeshua had told himâhow he would renounceÂŠ35876 Yeshua threeÂŠ35874 times before the rooster crowedâand he brokeÂŠ35879 down and cried.
\c 15
\s1 Pilate tries to interrogate Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Before Pilate; Jesus' Trial before Pilate
\r (Yhn 18:28-38; Mat. 27:1-2,11-14; Luke 23:1-5)
\p
\v 1 First thing in the morningÂŠ35887, the chiefÂŠ35893 priestsÂŠ35893 called a meeting with the eldersÂŠ35896 and the religiousÂŠ35900 teachersÂŠ35900 and all the councilÂŠ35905, and they ordered that \nd Yeshua\nd* be tied up and taken over to Governor PilateÂŠ35919.
\v 2 There PilateÂŠ35924 askedÂŠ35921 him, âAre you the kingÂŠ35929 of the Jews?â
\p â\wj You said itÂŠ35940,\wj*â replied Yeshua.
\p
\v 3 ThenÂŠ35941 the chiefÂŠ35946 priestsÂŠ35946 started hurling accusationsÂŠ35942 againstÂŠ35944 Yeshua,
\v 4 so PilateÂŠ35954 askedÂŠ35956 himÂŠ35958 again, âDon't you have anything to say? ListenÂŠ35964 to all these accusationsÂŠ35968 they're making against you.â
\p
\v 5 But PilateÂŠ35979 was astounded that \nd Yeshua\nd* didn't answerÂŠ35975 any further.
\s1 Pilate agrees to execute an innocent man
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Sentenced to Death; Pilate Hands Jesus over to Be Crucified
\r (Yhn 18:39â19:16; Mat. 27:15-26; Luke 23:13-25)
\p
\v 6 Now at time of the Jewish Passover, Pilate would normally pardon one prisonerÂŠ35991 for them andÂŠ35981 release him.
\v 7 There was another prisoner at the time named BarabbasÂŠ36003 who was an activist accused of murderÂŠ36013.
\v 8 By now, the crowdÂŠ36022 had arrived andÂŠ36017 asked Pilate to release a prisoner as usual at Passover,
\v 9 so he asked them, âDo you want me to release the KingÂŠ36043 of the Jews for you?â
\v 10 (This was because Pilate was well aware that the chiefÂŠ36058 priestsÂŠ36058 had brought Yeshua because they were jealous of his \add popularity\add*.)
\v 11 But the chiefÂŠ36061 priestsÂŠ36061 stirredÂŠ36063 up the crowdÂŠ36066 to start saying that it was BarabbasÂŠ36072 that they wanted released,
\v 12 so PilateÂŠ36077 asked againÂŠ36078, âThenÂŠ36076 what should I do with this man thatÂŠ36088 youÂŠ36089 call the KingÂŠ36091 of the Jews?â
\p
\v 13 The crowd yelledÂŠ36098 back, âExecuteÂŠ36101 himÂŠ36102 on a pole.â
\p
\v 14 âWhat has he even done wrong?â PilateÂŠ36105 demanded.
\p ButÂŠ36104 they just yelledÂŠ36117 louder, âExecuteÂŠ36120 him on a pole!â
\p
\v 15 Now PilateÂŠ36124 wanted to placate the crowdÂŠ36127, so he had BarabbasÂŠ36138 released while he had \nd Yeshua\nd* floggedÂŠ36145 andÂŠ36123 thenÂŠ36123 handed over to the executionÂŠ36148 squad.
\s1 The battalion plays with their mock âkingâ
\rem /s1 The Soldiers Make Fun of Jesus; The Soldiers Mock Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:2-3; Mat. 27:27-31)
\p
\v 16 SoÂŠ36150 the soldiersÂŠ36151 led Yeshua inside the palaceÂŠ36158 that was the governor'sÂŠ36162 residenceÂŠ36162, andÂŠ36163 called in the rest of the battalion.
\v 17 They \add mocked Yeshua\add* by dressingÂŠ36170 him in a kingly robe, andÂŠ36169 after someone twistedÂŠ36178 some thornsÂŠ36179 togetherÂŠ36178 into a mock crownÂŠ36180, they pressed it onto his head,
\v 18 andÂŠ36181 beganÂŠ36182 saluting himÂŠ36184, âGreetingsÂŠ36187, kingÂŠ36190 of the Jews.â
\v 19 They took turns whacking hisÂŠ36195 head with a stick and spittingÂŠ36204 on him, while others knelt down in front of him and pretended to be bowing to him.
\v 20 After they'd finished having fun mocking him, they took the purpleÂŠ36220 robe off him, andÂŠ36213 put hisÂŠ36227 own robe back on him. ThenÂŠ36213 they led him outside towards the executionÂŠ36235 spot.
\s1 Yeshua is publicly executed along with thieves
\rem /s1 The Crucifixion of Jesus; Jesus Is Crucified
\r (Yhn 19:17-27; Mat. 27:32-44; Luke 23:26-43)
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 15:21: \xt Rom 16:13.\x*As they walked out of the city, they came across a manÂŠ36241 comingÂŠ36247 in from the countryÂŠ36250. He was SimonÂŠ36243 from CyreneÂŠ36246, the fatherÂŠ36252 of AlexanderÂŠ36253 and RufusÂŠ36255, and the soldiers forced himÂŠ36260 to carryÂŠ36257 the executionÂŠ36259 pole,
\v 22 andÂŠ36261 so theyÂŠ36263 all arrived at GolgothaÂŠ36268 (whichÂŠ36270 means âPlaceÂŠ36275 of the skullÂŠ36275â).
\v 23 There the soldiers went to give some spiced wine to Yeshua, butÂŠ36286 heÂŠ36288 declined it.
\v 24 \x + \xo 15:24: \xt Psa 22:18.\x*SoÂŠ36289 theyÂŠ36294 carried out the executionÂŠ36290, taking Yeshua's clothesÂŠ36297 andÂŠ36304 drawing straws to see who would get what.
\v 25 By now itÂŠ36307 was around 9am, andÂŠ36312 theyÂŠ36314 affixed Yeshua to the pole.
\v 26 The chargeÂŠ36322 had been written out andÂŠ36316 attached \add at the top\add*: âThe kingÂŠ36328 of the Jews.â
\v 27 That morning, twoÂŠ36337 thieves were also executedÂŠ36334 thereâone on each side of Yeshua.
\p
\v 28 â
\v 29 \x + \xo 15:29: a \xt Psa 22:7; 109:25; \xo b \xt Yhn 2:19; Mrk 14:58.\x*As people passed by on the path, they insulted Yeshua, shakingÂŠ36365 theirÂŠ36368 headsÂŠ36367 and shouting, âHoy there! You who reckoned youÂŠ36373 could demolish the templeÂŠ36376 and rebuild itÂŠ36378 in threeÂŠ36380 daysÂŠ36381,
\v 30 comeÂŠ36387 down from that pole and saveÂŠ36383 yourselfÂŠ36384.â
\p
\v 31 SimilarlyÂŠ36391 the chiefÂŠ36395 priestsÂŠ36395 and the religiousÂŠ36402 teachersÂŠ36402 laughed together and mocked, âHe did miracles for othersÂŠ36404, but he can'tÂŠ36407 even saveÂŠ36409 himselfÂŠ36406.
\v 32 The so-called â\nd chosenÂŠ36411\nd* oneâ or âkingÂŠ36413 of Yisraelâ. Now, if he'd just comeÂŠ36416 down from there, thenÂŠ36427 we'd be able to believeÂŠ36425 him.â
\p Even the other two being executedÂŠ36429 with him were deridingÂŠ36432 him.
\s1 Yeshua breathes his last
\rem /s1 The Death of Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:28-30; Mat. 27:45-56; Luke 23:44-49)
\p
\v 33 At noon, it got dark everywhere, untilÂŠ36448 around 3pm,
\v 34 \x + \xo 15:34: \xt Psa 22:1.\x*when \nd Yeshua\nd* shoutedÂŠ36458 loudlyÂŠ36462, â\wj MyÂŠ36475 god, myÂŠ36475 god, why have you abandonedÂŠ36482 me?\wj*â
\p
\v 35 Some of the people standing nearby thought he was callingÂŠ36497 the prophet Eliyah \add (ElijahÂŠ36496)\add*.
\v 36 \x + \xo 15:36: \xt Psa 69:21.\x*One of them ran, and soaked a spongeÂŠ36507 in some sour wine, thenÂŠ36501 put it on a stick and held it up for Yeshua to drinkÂŠ36513, sayingÂŠ36515, âHang on. Let's seeÂŠ36519 if Eliyah does come to get him down.â
\p
\v 37 ButÂŠ36526 just thenÂŠ36526 \nd YeshuaÂŠ36527\nd* uttered a loudÂŠ36530 cryÂŠ36529 andÂŠ36526 exhaled his last breath.
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 15:38: \xt Exo 26:31-33.\x*(Back in the templeÂŠ36536, the curtainÂŠ36534 tore down the middle from the top to the bottomÂŠ36545.)
\v 39 WhenÂŠ36547 Yeshua died, the Roman centurionÂŠ36549 who had been standing back watching everything saidÂŠ36564, âThis manÂŠ36568 was definitely God's son.â
\p
\v 40 \x + \xo 15:40-41: \xt Luk 8:2-3.\x*Further back, there was also a group of womenÂŠ36579 observingÂŠ36582 everything. These included Maria from MagdalaÂŠ36589, Maria the motherÂŠ36600 of young Yacob and Yoses, and SalomeÂŠ36602,
\v 41 and others who had followedÂŠ36610 Yeshua around GalileeÂŠ36609 and helped look afterÂŠ36612 him, along with many others who had comeÂŠ36622 down with him to Yerushalem.
\s1 Yosef boldly lays the body in a burial chamber
\rem /s1 The Burial of Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:38-42; Mat. 27:57-61; Luke 23:50-56)
\p
\v 42 As eveningÂŠ36628 came, it was now the Preparation Day, i.e., the day before the Rest Day.
\v 43 Yosef (who'd comeÂŠ36641 from the city of ArimatheaÂŠ36646 and one who was waitingÂŠ36654 for the coming of God's kingdomÂŠ36656), a prominentÂŠ36647 councilÂŠ36648 memberÂŠ36648, steeled himselfÂŠ36652 up and wentÂŠ36661 in to see the governor to get permission to transfer \nd Yeshua's\nd* bodyÂŠ36669.
\v 44 Governor PilateÂŠ36674 didn't think he'd be dead yet, so he calledÂŠ36683 an army commander to find out if Yeshua had indeed died.
\v 45 As soon as he found out, he gave Yosef permission,
\v 46 so Yosef \add and his companions\add* went and boughtÂŠ36713 some linen burial cloth and thenÂŠ36710, removing Yeshua's body from the pole, wrappedÂŠ36721 it in the cloth and placed it in a burial chamber thatÂŠ36737 had been chiselled into a rockface. ThenÂŠ36710 they rolledÂŠ36744 a rockÂŠ36742 across the opening.
\v 47 Others were watching and noted whereÂŠ36772 the body had been laid, including Maria from MagdalaÂŠ36759 and Maria who was Yoses' motherÂŠ36762.
\c 16
\s1 The massive shock at the burial chamber
\rem /s1 The Resurrection of Jesus
\r (Yhn 20:1-10; Mat. 28:1-8; Luke 24:1-12)
\p
\v 1 After the Rest Day was over, Maria from MagdalaÂŠ36783 and Maria the motherÂŠ36786 of Yacob and SalomeÂŠ36790, went and boughtÂŠ36792 some traditional burial spicesÂŠ36793 that evening to take to the burial chamber and place with the body.
\v 2 ThenÂŠ36800 very earlyÂŠ36803 on Sunday morning theyÂŠ36811 went to the chamber, arriving just as the sunÂŠ36820 was rising.
\v 3 ButÂŠ36821 they realised that they didn't have anyone with them to roll the rockÂŠ36835 away that was covering the entrance.
\v 4 However, when they lookedÂŠ36847 they saw that the very largeÂŠ36863 rockÂŠ36860 had already been rolledÂŠ36854 away.
\v 5 SoÂŠ36866 they went on into the burial chamber andÂŠ36866 were totally stunned to find a youngÂŠ36874 manÂŠ36874 dressed in whiteÂŠ36882, sittingÂŠ36876 in there on the side.
\p
\v 6 He assured them, âDon't be surprised. I know you're lookingÂŠ36902 forÂŠ36902 \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethÂŠ36904\nd*, the one who was executedÂŠ36907 on a pole. ButÂŠ36888 seeÂŠ36912 there whereÂŠ36920 his body wasâhe's not there because he came back to life.
\v 7 \x + \xo 16:7: \xt Mat 26:32; Mrk 14:28.\x*So you three should go and tell hisÂŠ36929 apprenticesÂŠ36928, and PeterÂŠ36932 in particular, that he's going to go up ahead of them to GalileeÂŠ36940 and you'll all see him up thereÂŠ36941, just as he already told you.â
\p
\v 8 SoÂŠ36949 they left the chamber and took off running, still stunned and shaking and too scared to stop and to talk to anyoneÂŠ36969.
\rem It's not certain whether or not the following longer ending of this document was actually penned by the same author (Mark), or whether it was appended slightly later. Expert scholars are divided on this, and hence it's included here for your consideration:
\s1 \add The others don't believe that Maria saw Yeshua\add*
\rem /s1 AN OLD ENDING TO THE GOSPEL; THE LONGER ENDING OF MARK; Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
\r (Yhn 20:11-18; Mat. 28:9-10)
\rem /s2 [The most reliable early manuscripts and other ancient witnesses do not have Mark 16.9-20.]
\p
\v 9 \add After coming back to life early on Sunday morning, Yeshua appeared first to Maria from Magdala. (She was the one that he had once commanded seven demons to leave.)\add*
\v 10 \add After leaving him, she went and told his followers who were mourning and weeping at his loss.\add*
\v 11 \add But when she told them that he is alive again and that she'd seen him, they simply didn't believe her.\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua appears to two of his followers\add*
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Two Disciples; Jesus Appears to Two Followers
\r (Luke 24:13-35)
\p
\v 12 \add Later on, Yeshua appeared in a different form to two of his followers on the path as they left Yerushalem and headed out to the countryside,\add*
\v 13 \add but when they hurried back and told the others, no one believed them.\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua appears to his apprentices and instructs them\add*
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to the Eleven; Jesus Commissions the Disciples
\r (Yhn 20:19-23; Mat. 28:16-20; Luke 24:36-49; Acts 1:6-8)
\p
\v 14 \add Later again when the eleven apprentices were sitting around eating, Yeshua appeared in the room and scolded them for not believing and for being so stubborn when they hadn't believed others who had told them that he'd come back from the dead.\add*
\v 15 \add Then he instructed them, â\+wj Travel around all the world\x + \xo 16:15: \xt Acts 1:8.\x* and tell everyone the good message.\+wj*\add*
\v 16 \add \+wj Anyone who believes and gets immersed in water will be saved, however, those who refuse to believe will be condemned to death.\+wj*\add*
\v 17 \add \+wj Those who believe will be able to do miracles: they'll be able to use my authority to command demons to leave and to speak new languages,\+wj*\add*
\v 18 \add \+wj and they'll be able to pick up snakes. If they drink anything poisonous, it won't hurt them, and they will place their hands on people and make them better.\+wj*â\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua is lifted up to heaven\add*
\rem /s1 The Ascension of Jesus; Jesus Is Taken Up to Heaven
\r (Luke 24:50-53; Acts 1:9-11)
\p
\v 19 \add When Yeshua had finished speaking, he was lifted up into heaven and seated in the honoured place\x + \xo 16:19: \xt Acts 1:9-11.\x* next to God.\add*
\v 20 \add Then his followers went around preaching everywhere, and God worked through them and so they were able to confirm the truth of their preaching by doing miracles.\add*
